    "body": "<!-- Thank you for your contribution! Please follow these guidelines to enhance your pull request. If anything is unclear, submit your PR and reach out to maintainers for assistance. Join our Slack community at https://slack.sglang.io to discuss further. -->\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\n\r\nThere is currently an issue with the SGLang image dataset (random multimodal) where tokenization round-trip (initial tokens -> decode -> re-encode) is not deterministic, leading to different amount of tokens as specified in random-input-len. While running benchmark, the output reported only total input token counts — making it impossible to distinguish how many tokens came from raw text, chat template, tokenization round-trip overhead, or vision template. \r\n\r\nThis change prints a per-request token breakdown after dataset generation so users can immediately see where tokens come from.\r\n\r\n## Modifications\r\n- Added a **token breakdown summary** at the end of `sample_image_requests` that prints avg and total for:\r\n  - Raw text prompt tokens (the originally requested count, i.e. `input_lens`)\r\n  - Text prompt tokens after chat template application (`text_prompt_len` from `DatasetRow`)\r\n  - Text prompt overhead (difference: chat template + tokenization drift)\r\n  - Vision tokens (`vision_prompt_len` from `DatasetRow`)\r\n  \r\nExample output: \r\n\r\n> #Input tokens: 36676\r\n#Output tokens: 5120\r\n#Total images: 100\r\n#Images per request: 10 (fixed)\r\n=== Token Breakdown (per request avg / total) ===\r\n  Raw text prompt tokens (without overhead): avg=1024.0, total=10240\r\n  Text prompt tokens (with chat template): avg=1087.6, total=10876\r\n  Text prompt overhead: avg=63.6, total=636\r\n  Vision tokens: avg=2580.0, total=25800\r\n\r\n\r\n## Accuracy Tests\r\nN/A — This change only adds informational logging during benchmark dataset generation. No model output or inference logic is modified.\r\n\r\n## Speed Tests and Profiling\r\nN/A — No inference hot paths are affected. The added computation is a single numpy pass over already-collected data after the generation loop completes.\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n- [x] Format your code according to the [Format code with pre-commit](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#format-code-with-pre-commit).\r\n- [ ] Add unit tests according to the [Run and add unit tests](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#run-and-add-unit-tests).\r\n- [ ] Update documentation according to [Write documentations](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#write-documentations).\r\n- [ ] Provide accuracy and speed benchmark results according to [Test the accuracy](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#test-the-accuracy) and [Benchmark the speed](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#benchmark-the-speed).\r\n- [x] Follow the SGLang code style [guidance](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#code-style-guidance).\r\n\r\n\r\n## Review and Merge Process\r\n\r\n1. Ping Merge Oncalls to start the process. See the [PR Merge Process](https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/blob/main/.github/MAINTAINER.md#pull-request-merge-process).\r\n2. Get approvals from [CODEOWNERS](https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/blob/main/.github/CODEOWNERS) and other reviewers.\r\n3. Trigger CI tests with [comments](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#how-to-trigger-ci-tests) or contact authorized users to do so.\r\n   - Common commands include `/tag-and-rerun-ci`, `/tag-run-ci-label`, `/rerun-failed-ci`\r\n4. After green CI and required approvals, ask Merge Oncalls or people with Write permission to merge the PR.\r\n",
